<A HREF="http://www.geocities.com/TimesSquare/Labyrinth/1868"><I><FONT FACE="Tahoma" SIZE=2 COLOR="#ffffff">Knights of Phoenix</I></FONT></A><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubiasschmias.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bias Schmias</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Tad-pole</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>61</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>12/8/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFF00>3:32:21 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: FYI regarding KoP in Hate on Monday</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Edwina, reading the rules of the calendar and the intent, I get a couple of different takes.  I'll set out what I see, and then end with what I think the 'correct' answer is from where I sit.<br>
<br>
Bare text of the rule:<br>
<br>
&quot;You may invite whoever you wish along on your raids, as long as no more than 6 come from the same guild&quot;<br>
<br>
My Interpretation:  Well ... the rule isn't exactly OPEN for interpretation at this point, now is it? 8P<br>
<br>
Relevant section from the 'Intent' paragraph:<br>
<br>
Of course you may invite friends on raids. ... What you may NOT do is use your relationship with another posting entity so that you all may go twice per round. If you have another guild you are always teaming with, you need to form an alliance and in this way you are only entitled to one day per round, like everyone else.<br>
<br>
My Interpretation:<br>
The key here is &quot;Another posting entity&quot;.  Since the guild you are inviting 7 people from does not fall under that heading, my interpretation of the intent of the rule is that you are within the parameters of what everyone envisioned.<br>
<br>
The next sentence can be ambiguious, though.  is this a guild that you are 'always' teaming with? (The question of what does 'always' mean comes to mind ... heh.)  If it is, then what should probably happen is either a cessation for a few weeks of teaming, or else add them to the alliance for your posting rights.  Strictly for that.  I'm not saying you should be required to 'ally' with some guild just because you always go on raids. Just that you should both be listed as the same posting entity, for the sake of Ye Olde Fairness.<br>
<br>
Short Version Of The Above, and what I think should be The Answer (subject to review by all ubers, because of course they control what we all think and do.  FEAR THEIR IRON GRIP AND HELLISH RAVENING BEAKS!!!  or something.)<br>
<br>
The '6 max from a guild' rule as originally written was intended as '6 max invitations from a single guild that is also a posting entity.'  That way you could (if you were to choose) host a &quot;help this one guild&quot; night in a plane, and take up all 25+ of their members and run 'em thru Fear/Hate/Sky, provided they could not post a date on their own.<br>
<br>
This does bring up another variation on this rule, and one we should probably clarify just to avoid arguments.<br>
<br>
Situation a (Your situation, edwina)<br>
non-posting guild invites x 7<br>
j.random.player invites x 7<br>
<br>
Acceptable? I say yes.<br>
<br>
Situation b<br>
posting alliance 1, guild a invites x 5<br>
posting alliance 1, guild b invites x 3<br>
<br>
Acceptable?  This doesn't break the '6 from a guild' rule, but it does seem to violate the intent of 'no more than 6 invites from a posting entity/guild'<br>
<br>
Situation c<br>
posting alliance 1, guild a invites x 3<br>
posting alliance 1, guild a invites x 3<br>
posting alliance 1, unguilded members of alliance invites x 3<br>
<br>
Acceptable?  Similar situation.  And if someone like Clept ever gets off their butt to help the supposedly disenfranchised 'nonguilded players' form a posting alliance, this is a likely scenario.<br>
<br>
If we all know what the intent/spirit of the rule is, then let's reword it.  Not because it needs to be changed (it doesn't) but because it could use a hair of clarification to prevent disputes or abuses.<br>
<br>
And thanks a bazillion for bringing this up Edwina.  You could have (I'm sure) run your raid with 7 people from another (non-posting) guild and not caused the slightest ruckus.  Very good of you to bring this issue up ahead of time.<br>
<br>
Regardless of whatever else is decided, I think Edwina &amp; Co. should take their 7 up on their raid since there's some ambiguity in the rule.  We can argue for the next few weeks over what the definition of 'is' is while they raid.<br>
<br>
